cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel network architecture and loss function, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with feature extraction and fusion, which are related to multimedia processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves regularization techniques, which are related to optimization and generalization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with security and privacy issues related to person re-identification, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
